                        &lt;p&gt;Agree with Gabriele&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The important question you should ask is: &#039;What is the goal/outcome of the the event?&#039;  A hackathon can be an amazing event, but it has a different goal  (and drives different behavior) than code retreat.  In particular, everyone being under time pressure to deliver functioning apps and each group working in a different problem domain tends to reduce opportunities for shared learning.&lt;/p&gt;
